**Phase 2: Rendering & Navigation**

Create the core Document model that holds parsed markdown and all associated indices.

**Background:**
The Document is the central domain model. It holds:
- Source text and metadata
- Parse results (headings, links, sections, anchors)
- Line map for position conversions
- Display cache (added later in this phase)

This is a pure domain object with no UI concerns.

**Document Model:**

```rust
pub struct Document {
    pub id: DocumentId,              // Unique ID for this doc instance
    pub path: Option<PathBuf>,       // File path (None for stdin)
    pub source_kind: SourceKind,
    pub source: Arc<str>,            // Immutable source text
    pub checksum: u64,               // For change detection
    pub lines: Arc<[LineRecord]>,    // Line map
    pub headings: Arc<[Heading]>,    // Sorted by line
    pub links: Arc<[LinkRef]>,       // All links in document
    pub sections: Arc<[Section]>,    // Section boundaries
    pub anchors: AnchorIndex,        // Slug -> target mapping
}

pub enum SourceKind {
    File { canonical_path: PathBuf },
    Stdin,
    Fixture { name: String },
}

pub struct DocumentId(pub Uuid);
```

**Construction:**
```rust
impl Document {
    pub fn from_path(path: PathBuf) -> Result<Self, Error> {
        let source = fs::read_to_string(&path)?;
        Self::from_source(source, SourceKind::File { canonical_path })
    }

    pub fn from_stdin(source: String) -> Result<Self, Error> {
        Self::from_source(source, SourceKind::Stdin)
    }

