**Why Arc<[T]>?**
- Immutable after construction
- Cheap to clone (reference counting)
- Can be shared across threads (future: parallel search)
- More cache-friendly than Vec

**DocumentId:**
- Use UUID for global uniqueness
- Enables tracking documents across sessions
- Session restore can reference doc by ID
- History stack references docs by ID

**Checksum:**
- Use xxhash or similar for fast hashing
- Detect if file changed on disk
- Enables smart reload (skip if unchanged)

**State Management:**
The Document lives in:
```rust
struct DocumentSession {
    doc: Arc<Document>,
    cursor_line: usize,
    top_line: usize,
    // viewport state per document
}

struct Model {
    doc_stack: Vec<DocumentSession>,  // Navigation history
    current_doc: usize,                // Index into doc_stack
    // ...
}
```

**Error Handling:**
- FileReadError: file not found, permission denied
- ParseError: invalid UTF-8
- IOError: disk read failures

**Testing:**
- Load document from file
- Load document from stdin
- Verify all indices are populated
- Test reload detection (checksum)
- Test error cases (missing file, invalid UTF-8)

**Acceptance:**
- Can construct Document from file and stdin
- All indices (headings, links, sections, anchors, lines) populated
- Reload works and detects changes
- Tests pass for all construction paths

